2.00	Intracellular_signaling_pathway	Signal transduction	Signal transduction occurs when an extracellular signaling molecule activates a cell surface receptor. In turn, this receptor alters intracellular molecules creating a response. There are two stages in this process:	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Signal_transduction_pathways.svg/220px-Signal_transduction_pathways.svg.png
